### Description

A lot of Pages or custom Layouts/Views are done in XAML today often with no actual code behind. With XamlC turned on we should be able to eliminate the cs file completely since XamlC is generating the class for us. The behavior should allow for flexibility as the developer needs so that if your entire class looks like:

```cs
public class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
    }
}
```

you should be able to simply delete the file and have all of your code continue to work.

