### Description
If a UI Test isn't in the *Xamarin.Forms.Controls.Issues* namespace and you run that as the first UI Test then this code doesn't run

```
#if UITEST
namespace Xamarin.Forms.Controls.Issues
{
	using System;
	using NUnit.Framework;

	// Run setup once for all tests in the Xamarin.Forms.Controls.Issues namespace
	// (instead of once for each test)
	[SetUpFixture]
	public class IssuesSetup
	{
		[SetUp]
		public void RunBeforeAnyTests()
		{
			AppSetup.RunningApp = AppSetup.Setup(null);
		}
	}
}
#endif
```

And you get a Null Reference Exception
https://github.com/xamarin/Xamarin.Forms/pull/4144#discussion_r226783148


### Steps to Reproduce

1.  Find a UI Test
2.  change the namespace to namespace Xamarin.Forms.Controls
3. Try to run the UI Test

### Expected Behavior
Make it easier for contributors to add UI Tests to existing issues and not have them fail
